###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03414374
obo:FOODON_03414374 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf obo:FOODON_03414381 ;
                    obo:IAO_0000115 "The biological subfamily *Bovinae* includes a diverse group of 10 genera of medium- to large-sized ungulates, including domestic cattle, the bison, African buffalo, the water buffalo, the yak, and the four-horned and spiral-horned antelopes. The evolutionary relationship between the members of the group is obscure, and their classification into loose tribes rather than formal subgroups reflects this uncertainty. General characteristics include cloven hoofs and usually at least one of the sexes of a species having true horns."@en ;
                    obo:IAO_0000119 "WIKIPEDIA:Bovinae" ;
                    obo:IAO_0000412 obo:foodon.owl ;
                    oboInOwl:hasSynonym "bovinae"@en ;
                    rdfs:label "bovine"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03414381
obo:FOODON_03414381 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf obo:FOODON_00005680 ,
                                    obo:FOODON_03411134 ;
                    obo:IAO_0000115 """A bovid (family *Bovidae*) is any of almost 140 species of cloven-hoofed, ruminant mammal which has males with characteristic unbranching horns covered in a permanent sheath of keratin.

The family is widespread, being native to Asia, Africa, Europe and North America, and diverse: members include bison, African buffalo, water buffalo, antelopes, gazelles, sheep, goats, muskoxen, and domestic cattle."""@en ;
                    obo:IAO_0000119 "WIKIPEDIA:Bovidae" ;
                    obo:IAO_0000412 obo:foodon.owl ;
                    oboInOwl:hasSynonym "bovidae"@en ;
                    rdfs:label "bovid"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03420106
obo:FOODON_03420106 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf obo:FOODON_03420218 ;
                    obo:IAO_0000412 obo:foodon.owl ;
                    rdfs:label "digestive system organ"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03420116
obo:FOODON_03420116 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf obo:BFO_0000040 ;
                    obo:IAO_0000115 "Material which is distinguished primarily by the organism(s) it derives from."@en ;
                    obo:IAO_0000116 "This was renamed from \"part of organism\" (and from LanguaL's original \"part of plant or animal\") to encompass organism material that is produced by an animal or plant rather than \"part of\" it, such as an egg, and might not be countable per se, such as milk. Additionally the existing definition's \"from which a food product or its major ingredient is derived.\"was removed as an unnecessary constraint. [2023/03/02]"@en ;
                    obo:IAO_0000412 obo:foodon.owl ;
                    rdfs:comment "LanguaL curation note: \"e.g. *LEAF*, *ROOT OR TUBER*, *ORGAN MEAT*, *MILK* OR *EGG*; it also includes components of parts, such as *CREAM*, and extracts, concentrates or isolates, such as *PROTEIN EXTRACT* or *SUGAR*.\""@en ,
                                 "Old definition as of Feb 25, 2025: Anatomical or other part(s) or substances derived from plant or animal or fungal organisms."@en ;
                    rdfs:label "organism material"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03420122
obo:FOODON_03420122 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf obo:FOODON_00004332 ;
                    obo:IAO_0000115 "A piece of an animal which is not meat, namely a bone, feather, shell, skin or trim fat."@en ;
                    obo:IAO_0000412 obo:foodon.owl ;
                    rdfs:comment "LanguaL curation note: *BLOOD* AND *INK, AQUATIC ANIMAL* are now listed under organism substance."@en ;
                    rdfs:label "nonmeat part of animal"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03420127
obo:FOODON_03420127 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf obo:FOODON_03420164 ;
                    obo:IAO_0000412 obo:foodon.owl ;
                    rdfs:comment """This is from a LanguaL \"ANIMAL BODY OR BODY PART\" class. Its subclasses can be used if it is ambiguous what animal is being referred to, and whether the reference is being made to a whole animal or some part of it, including parts of organs.  However, see if a more precise term is available under either the \"animal carcass\" branch or the \"piece of animal\"branch.

LanguaL curation note: Includes carcass meat, organ meat, and nonmeat parts of animals, as well as the whole animal."""@en ;
                    rdfs:label "animal (whole or piece(s))"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03420129
obo:FOODON_03420129 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf obo:FOODON_03420218 ;
                    obo:IAO_0000412 obo:foodon.owl ;
                    rdfs:label "cardiovascular system organ"@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/FOODON_03420144
obo:FOODON_03420144 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                    rdfs:subClassOf obo:FOODON_03420148 ;
                    obo:IAO_0000412 obo:foodon.owl ;
                    rdfs:comment "LanguaL curation note: This broad term is used for the plant as a whole, excluding the root and the fruit; for any piece consisting of two or more individual parts (e.g., a celery stalk with the leaf blades attached); or for any mixture of two or more individual parts (e.g., mushroom stems and pieces)."@en ;
                    rdfs:label "plant above surface, excluding fruit and seed"@en .


